\noindent\textbf{[2018 Oct/Nov, 0580/42, Question 10]}\par

\begin{parts}
\item The lake behind a dam has an area of 55 hectares.
When the gates in the dam are open, water flows out at a rate of 75000 litres per second.

\begin{subparts}
\item Show that 90 million litres of water flows out in 20 minutes.

[1]

\item Beneath the surface, the lake has vertical sides.
Calculate the drop in the water level of the lake when the gates are open for 20 minutes.
Give your answer in centimetres.
[1 hectare = 10$^{4}$ m$^{2}$, 1000 litres = 1 m$^{3}$]

\AnswerLine[][] cm
\Marks{3}

