\item A solid metal cone has radius 10 cm and height 36 cm.

\begin{subparts}
\item Calculate the volume of this cone.
[The volume, V, of a cone with radius r and height h is V = $\dfrac{1}{3}\pi r^{2}h$.]

\AnswerLine[][] cm$^{3}$
